"title": "8715: dishonesty, and God's nature",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8715",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Dishonesty is contrary to the will and nature of God, and so should not be found among the people of God.</p>\n<h2>Dishonesty is contrary to the will and nature of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num23:19\">NUM 23:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:29\">1SA 15:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:4\">ROM 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:2\">TIT 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Dishonesty, like sin, is of satanic origin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:44\">JHN 8:44</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:1-Gen3:5\">GEN 3:1–3:5</a></p>\n<h2>God's hatred of dishonesty</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:22\">PRO 12:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:4-Ps5:6\">PSA 5:4–5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:16-Prov6:17\">PRO 6:16–6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:1-Isa59:4\">ISA 59:1–59:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:12-Isa59:15\">ISA 59:12–59:15</a></p>\n<h2>Kinds of dishonesty</h2>\n<h3>In business deals</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:7\">HOS 12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:13-Deut25:16\">DEU 25:13–25:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:14\">PRO 20:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos8:5\">AMO 8:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:10\">MIC 6:10</a></p>\n<h3>In not paying debts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:21\">PSA 37:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4\">JAS 5:4</a></p>\n<h3>In exploiting the poor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek22:29\">EZK 22:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job24:2-Job24:11\">JOB 24:2–24:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:7\">ISA 32:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:13\">JER 22:13</a></p>\n<h2>God's judgment on dishonesty</h2>\n<h3>God's denunciation of dishonesty in general</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:1-Hos4:2\">HOS 4:1–4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:15\">LEV 19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:8-Jer7:10\">JER 7:8–7:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:6\">1TH 4:6</a></p>\n<h3>The dishonesty of liars and false witnesses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:9\">PRO 19:9</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:10\">ACT 5:1–5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:16-Deut19:19\">DEU 19:16–19:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:10-Josh7:12\">JOS 7:10–7:12</a> <em>regarding Achan's sin</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs5:19-2Kgs5:27\">2KI 5:19–5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:6\">PSA 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa29:20-Isa29:21\">ISA 29:20–29:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:4-Jer9:9\">JER 9:4–9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:8\">REV 21:8</a></p>\n<h3>The dishonesty of false prophets and teachers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer14:14-Jer14:15\">JER 14:14–14:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:1-2Pet2:3\">2PE 2:1–2:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:14-Isa9:15\">ISA 9:14–9:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer28:15-Jer28:16\">JER 28:15–28:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:1-Ezek13:23\">EZK 13:1–13:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:2-Zech10:3\">ZEC 10:2–10:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:1-1Tim4:2\">1TI 4:1–4:2</a></p>\n<h2>God's demands for making amends for dishonesty</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:1-Lev6:7\">LEV 6:1–6:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:12-Luke3:14\">LUK 3:12–3:14</a> <em>This demonstrated that their repentance was genuine</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8\">LUK 19:8</a> <em>the result of encountering Jesus Christ</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:1-Luke16:12\">LUK 16:1–16:12</a> <em>Jesus Christ was not commending the steward's dishonesty but his shrewdness.</em></p>",
